  "source": "Bulbapedia: Character encoding (Generation I), Text entry (Generation I)",
  "notes": "Italian+Spanish shared encoding. Differs from English at 0xBA-0xBF (accented vowels instead of English contractions), 0xC0-0xDE (accented characters, ordinal, ampersand, and contractions instead of blanks), and 0xE4-0xE5 (inverted question/exclamation marks instead of 'r and 'm). The naming screen is identical to English (no accented characters or special Spanish/Italian glyphs are enterable); all accented characters and contractions are decode-only (appear in dialogue and species names but not on the naming screen).",
